---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<BaseLayout
  lang="en"
  title="The Lonelots Tool – Job Evaluation and Pay Audit"
  description="The Lonelots tool is a weighted multi-factor and gender-neutral job evaluation tool. Free to download. Includes job evaluation and pay audit functions."
  ogImage={`${base}/images/Analys-lönelots.jpg`}
>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="relative min-h-[60vh] flex items-center justify-center overflow-hidden">
    <img src={`${base}/images/Analys-lönelots.jpg`} alt="" class="absolute inset-0 w-full h-full object-cover" />
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-brand-red/70"></div>
    <div class="relative z-10 max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 text-center text-white">
      <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-medium uppercase tracking-wider mb-6">
        The Lonelots Tool
      </h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-white/90 max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-4">
        A weighted multi-factor and gender-neutral job evaluation tool
        that you can download free of charge.
      </p>
      <p class="text-white/70 max-w-2xl mx-auto mb-8">
        The tool consists of two parts: a job evaluation system to assess which work is equivalent
        and a pay audit tool that provides the tables and charts needed to map and analyse wages
        in equal and equivalent work.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center">
        <a href="#download" class="inline-block bg-white text-brand-text font-medium px-8 py-3 uppercase tracking-wider text-sm hover:bg-brand-gray transition-colors">
          Download
        </a>
        <a href="#job-evaluation" class="inline-block border-2 border-white text-white font-medium px-8 py-3 uppercase tracking-wider text-sm hover:bg-white/10 transition-colors">
          Get started
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Download -->
  <section id="download" class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium text-brand-text uppercase tracking-wider mb-8 text-center">Download</h2>
      <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        <p class="text-brand-text/70 mb-6 text-center">
          Version 7.1 – free for all organisations, large and small.
        </p>
        <!-- DOWNLOAD LINKS — Do NOT edit these URLs!
             Filenames must match the files uploaded to GitHub Releases.
             For new versions: contact Emil to update the links. -->
        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center mb-8">
          <a href="https://github.com/Trollvik/lonelotsarna/releases/latest/download/LoneLots-7.1-EN.exe"
            class="flex items-center justify-center gap-2 bg-brand-red text-white font-medium px-6 py-3 uppercase tracking-wider text-sm hover:bg-brand-red-dark transition-colors">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 10v6m0 0l-3-3m3 3l3-3m2 8H7a2 2 0 01-2-2V5a2 2 0 012-2h5.586a1 1 0 01.707.293l5.414 5.414a1 1 0 01.293.707V19a2 2 0 01-2 2z" /></svg>
            Download for PC
          </a>
          <a href="https://github.com/Trollvik/lonelotsarna/releases/latest/download/lonelots-mac-7.1-arm64-EN.dmg"
            class="flex items-center justify-center gap-2 bg-brand-red text-white font-medium px-6 py-3 uppercase tracking-wider text-sm hover:bg-brand-red-dark transition-colors">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 10v6m0 0l-3-3m3 3l3-3m2 8H7a2 2 0 01-2-2V5a2 2 0 012-2h5.586a1 1 0 01.707.293l5.414 5.414a1 1 0 01.293.707V19a2 2 0 01-2 2z" /></svg>
            Download for Mac
          </a>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-amber-50 border-l-4 border-amber-400 p-4 mb-8">
          <p class="text-sm text-amber-800">
            <strong>Important!</strong> If you have used Lonelots before and have saved evaluations,
            you must first make backups before installing the new version. Saved data is not
            automatically transferred.
          </p>
        </div>
        <details class="border-b border-gray-200 pb-4">
          <summary class="cursor-pointer py-3 text-brand-text font-medium uppercase tracking-wider text-sm flex items-center justify-between hover:text-brand-red transition-colors">
            Installation instructions
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 shrink-0 transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 6v12m6-6H6" /></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="pt-2 pb-4 text-brand-text/70">
            <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2">
              <li>Download the installation file above.</li>
              <li>Double-click the downloaded file to install Lonelots.</li>
              <li>Follow the instructions when the installer starts.</li>
              <li>If you see "Windows has protected your computer", click "More information" then "Run anyway".</li>
              <li>An icon will be created on your desktop. Double-click to start.</li>
            </ol>
          </div>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Job Evaluation -->
  <section id="job-evaluation" class="py-16 bg-brand-gray">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium text-brand-text uppercase tracking-wider mb-4 text-center">
        <span class="text-brand-red">Part 1:</span> Job Evaluation
      </h2>
      <p class="text-brand-text/70 text-center max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-10">
        The job evaluation system is based on the main areas of the Swedish Discrimination Act –
        knowledge and skills, responsibility, effort, and working conditions. You customise the
        system by adapting factors, levels, and weighting to your organisation.
      </p>
      <div class="space-y-0 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <details class="group border-b border-gray-200 bg-white">
          <summary class="cursor-pointer p-5 flex items-center gap-4 hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors">
            <span class="flex items-center justify-center w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-brand-red text-white text-sm font-medium shrink-0">1</span>
            <span class="font-medium text-brand-text uppercase tracking-wider text-sm">Preparation</span>
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 ml-auto shrink-0 text-brand-text/40 transition-transform group-open:rotate-45" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 6v12m6-6H6" /></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-5 pb-5 pt-0 text-brand-text/70 text-sm leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>Decide who will participate and how the work should be organised. Compile information about the different positions to be evaluated.</p>
            <p>The evaluation should be done by at least three people, women and men, with good knowledge of the organisation. They should not represent group interests but use their judgement and available documentation.</p>
            <p>Agree with trade unions on how to collaborate. They should have the opportunity to participate in the pay survey, analysis, and action planning.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="group border-b border-gray-200 bg-white">
          <summary class="cursor-pointer p-5 flex items-center gap-4 hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors">
            <span class="flex items-center justify-center w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-brand-red text-white text-sm font-medium shrink-0">2</span>
            <span class="font-medium text-brand-text uppercase tracking-wider text-sm">Adapt factor plan</span>
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 ml-auto shrink-0 text-brand-text/40 transition-transform group-open:rotate-45" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 6v12m6-6H6" /></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-5 pb-5 pt-0 text-brand-text/70 text-sm leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>Factors can be added or removed. The number of levels can be adjusted between 2–7. The system is a basic model designed to be adapted to different organisations.</p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1">
              <li>Review wording to match your organisation's values and direction.</li>
              <li>Keep factors simple. Less complexity makes evaluation easier.</li>
              <li>If an aspect is particularly important, consider making it a separate factor.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="group border-b border-gray-200 bg-white">
          <summary class="cursor-pointer p-5 flex items-center gap-4 hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors">
            <span class="flex items-center justify-center w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-brand-red text-white text-sm font-medium shrink-0">3</span>
            <span class="font-medium text-brand-text uppercase tracking-wider text-sm">Weighting</span>
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 ml-auto shrink-0 text-brand-text/40 transition-transform group-open:rotate-45" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 6v12m6-6H6" /></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-5 pb-5 pt-0 text-brand-text/70 text-sm leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>Weighting means balancing the different factors against each other. Distribute 100 percent between them to reflect what is valued in your organisation.</p>
            <p>Weighting can be done after the evaluation. The evaluation process often provides better understanding of the factors' relative importance.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="group border-b border-gray-200 bg-white">
          <summary class="cursor-pointer p-5 flex items-center gap-4 hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors">
            <span class="flex items-center justify-center w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-brand-red text-white text-sm font-medium shrink-0">4</span>
            <span class="font-medium text-brand-text uppercase tracking-wider text-sm">Jobs to evaluate</span>
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 ml-auto shrink-0 text-brand-text/40 transition-transform group-open:rotate-45" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 6v12m6-6H6" /></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-5 pb-5 pt-0 text-brand-text/70 text-sm leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>Enter all jobs to be evaluated with an optional statistics code. You can write or paste a job description in the text field.</p>
            <p>Use the "Classification" feature to divide the evaluation into smaller groups if you have many different jobs.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="group border-b border-gray-200 bg-white">
          <summary class="cursor-pointer p-5 flex items-center gap-4 hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors">
            <span class="flex items-center justify-center w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-brand-red text-white text-sm font-medium shrink-0">5</span>
            <span class="font-medium text-brand-text uppercase tracking-wider text-sm">Evaluation sheets</span>
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 ml-auto shrink-0 text-brand-text/40 transition-transform group-open:rotate-45" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 6v12m6-6H6" /></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-5 pb-5 pt-0 text-brand-text/70 text-sm leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>All jobs are shown in evaluation sheets where the evaluation is done factor by factor. Write a brief justification for each placement.</p>
            <p>It is the job requirements, not the individual's ability, that should be evaluated. Remember to save regularly and make backups.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="group border-b border-gray-200 bg-white">
          <summary class="cursor-pointer p-5 flex items-center gap-4 hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors">
            <span class="flex items-center justify-center w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-brand-red text-white text-sm font-medium shrink-0">6</span>
            <span class="font-medium text-brand-text uppercase tracking-wider text-sm">Results</span>
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 ml-auto shrink-0 text-brand-text/40 transition-transform group-open:rotate-45" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 6v12m6-6H6" /></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-5 pb-5 pt-0 text-brand-text/70 text-sm leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>Review the unweighted and weighted scores. Does the result reflect your organisation's intentions? Have the Discrimination Act requirements been met?</p>
            <p>The analysis may lead to changes in factor content, weighting adjustments, or re-evaluation of specific assessments.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="group border-b border-gray-200 bg-white">
          <summary class="cursor-pointer p-5 flex items-center gap-4 hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors">
            <span class="flex items-center justify-center w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-brand-red text-white text-sm font-medium shrink-0">7</span>
            <span class="font-medium text-brand-text uppercase tracking-wider text-sm">Grouping equivalent jobs</span>
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 ml-auto shrink-0 text-brand-text/40 transition-transform group-open:rotate-45" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 6v12m6-6H6" /></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-5 pb-5 pt-0 text-brand-text/70 text-sm leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>Divide the results into score intervals or clusters. Jobs within the same interval are considered equivalent. A suitable interval is typically 5 to 10 points.</p>
            <p>When the overall result is considered fair and reasonable, it is time for the pay survey.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Pay Survey -->
  <section id="pay-survey" class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium text-brand-text uppercase tracking-wider mb-4 text-center">
        <span class="text-brand-red">Part 2:</span> Pay Review
      </h2>
      <p class="text-brand-text/70 text-center max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-10">
        The tool includes the features required to conduct a pay survey in accordance with the
        Swedish Discrimination Act. It is a tool for comparing and analysing salaries in equal
        and equivalent jobs and highlighting structural pay disparities.
      </p>
      <div class="space-y-0 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <details class="group border-b border-gray-200 bg-brand-gray">
          <summary class="cursor-pointer p-5 flex items-center gap-4 hover:bg-gray-100 transition-colors">
            <span class="flex items-center justify-center w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-brand-red text-white text-sm font-medium shrink-0">1</span>
            <span class="font-medium text-brand-text uppercase tracking-wider text-sm">Analyse practices and regulations</span>
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 ml-auto shrink-0 text-brand-text/40 transition-transform group-open:rotate-45" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 6v12m6-6H6" /></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-5 pb-5 pt-0 text-brand-text/70 text-sm leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>Start by evaluating the previous year's action plan. Then review pay regulations: collective agreements, pay policy, criteria for individual pay setting, bonuses, and benefits.</p>
            <p>The review should determine whether rules are gender-neutral and applied equally to women and men.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="group border-b border-gray-200 bg-brand-gray">
          <summary class="cursor-pointer p-5 flex items-center gap-4 hover:bg-gray-100 transition-colors">
            <span class="flex items-center justify-center w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-brand-red text-white text-sm font-medium shrink-0">2</span>
            <span class="font-medium text-brand-text uppercase tracking-wider text-sm">Prepare salary data</span>
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 ml-auto shrink-0 text-brand-text/40 transition-transform group-open:rotate-45" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 6v12m6-6H6" /></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-5 pb-5 pt-0 text-brand-text/70 text-sm leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>Create an Excel salary file with employee and pay data. Required columns: personal ID number (10 digits, penultimate digit indicates gender), job title or statistics code, group (if not using Lonelots evaluation), and full-time monthly salary.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="group border-b border-gray-200 bg-brand-gray">
          <summary class="cursor-pointer p-5 flex items-center gap-4 hover:bg-gray-100 transition-colors">
            <span class="flex items-center justify-center w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-brand-red text-white text-sm font-medium shrink-0">3</span>
            <span class="font-medium text-brand-text uppercase tracking-wider text-sm">Create pay survey</span>
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 ml-auto shrink-0 text-brand-text/40 transition-transform group-open:rotate-45" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 6v12m6-6H6" /></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-5 pb-5 pt-0 text-brand-text/70 text-sm leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>Import the salary file. If you have done a job evaluation in Lonelots, link it by choosing "Use groups from current job evaluation". Otherwise, specify groups in the Excel file.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="group border-b border-gray-200 bg-brand-gray">
          <summary class="cursor-pointer p-5 flex items-center gap-4 hover:bg-gray-100 transition-colors">
            <span class="flex items-center justify-center w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-brand-red text-white text-sm font-medium shrink-0">4</span>
            <span class="font-medium text-brand-text uppercase tracking-wider text-sm">Analyse equal work</span>
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 ml-auto shrink-0 text-brand-text/40 transition-transform group-open:rotate-45" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 6v12m6-6H6" /></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-5 pb-5 pt-0 text-brand-text/70 text-sm leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>Analyse differences in pay, pay distribution, and pay development for women and men doing equal work. All pay differences must be explained with objective reasons unrelated to gender.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="group border-b border-gray-200 bg-brand-gray">
          <summary class="cursor-pointer p-5 flex items-center gap-4 hover:bg-gray-100 transition-colors">
            <span class="flex items-center justify-center w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-brand-red text-white text-sm font-medium shrink-0">5</span>
            <span class="font-medium text-brand-text uppercase tracking-wider text-sm">Analyse equivalent work</span>
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 ml-auto shrink-0 text-brand-text/40 transition-transform group-open:rotate-45" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 6v12m6-6H6" /></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-5 pb-5 pt-0 text-brand-text/70 text-sm leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>Compare pay in female-dominated jobs with non-female-dominated jobs in the same equivalence group. A job is considered female-dominated if more than 60% of workers are women.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="group border-b border-gray-200 bg-brand-gray">
          <summary class="cursor-pointer p-5 flex items-center gap-4 hover:bg-gray-100 transition-colors">
            <span class="flex items-center justify-center w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-brand-red text-white text-sm font-medium shrink-0">6</span>
            <span class="font-medium text-brand-text uppercase tracking-wider text-sm">Document</span>
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 ml-auto shrink-0 text-brand-text/40 transition-transform group-open:rotate-45" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 6v12m6-6H6" /></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-5 pb-5 pt-0 text-brand-text/70 text-sm leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>Employers with at least ten employees must document the pay survey. Documentation should include results, required adjustments, cost estimates, and a timeline. Adjustments must be implemented within three years.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="group border-b border-gray-200 bg-brand-gray">
          <summary class="cursor-pointer p-5 flex items-center gap-4 hover:bg-gray-100 transition-colors">
            <span class="flex items-center justify-center w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-brand-red text-white text-sm font-medium shrink-0">7</span>
            <span class="font-medium text-brand-text uppercase tracking-wider text-sm">Areas of use</span>
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 ml-auto shrink-0 text-brand-text/40 transition-transform group-open:rotate-45" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 6v12m6-6H6" /></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-5 pb-5 pt-0 text-brand-text/70 text-sm leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p><strong>Equal pay:</strong> Annual pay surveys discover, correct, and prevent unjustified pay differences.</p>
            <p><strong>Pay criteria:</strong> A tailored job evaluation system provides a good basis for individual pay criteria and better quality salary conversations.</p>
            <p><strong>Organisational development:</strong> The analysis highlights ambiguities in work organisation and accountability.</p>
            <p><strong>Attractive employer:</strong> An equal-pay employer attracts talent and gives employees confidence in their development and expectations.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Guidelines -->
  <section class="py-12 bg-brand-gray">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium text-brand-text uppercase tracking-wider mb-8 text-center">Guidelines</h2>
      <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center">
        <a href={`${base}/documents/job-evaluation-guideline-2025.pdf`} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 bg-brand-red text-white font-medium px-6 py-3 uppercase tracking-wider text-sm hover:bg-brand-red-dark transition-colors">
          <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 10v6m0 0l-3-3m3 3l3-3m2 8H7a2 2 0 01-2-2V5a2 2 0 012-2h5.586a1 1 0 01.707.293l5.414 5.414a1 1 0 01.293.707V19a2 2 0 01-2 2z" /></svg>
          Job Evaluation Guideline (PDF)
        </a>
        <a href={`${base}/documents/pay-survey-guideline-2025.pdf`} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 bg-brand-red text-white font-medium px-6 py-3 uppercase tracking-wider text-sm hover:bg-brand-red-dark transition-colors">
          <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 10v6m0 0l-3-3m3 3l3-3m2 8H7a2 2 0 01-2-2V5a2 2 0 012-2h5.586a1 1 0 01.707.293l5.414 5.414a1 1 0 01.293.707V19a2 2 0 01-2 2z" /></svg>
          Pay Survey Guideline (PDF)
        </a>
      </div>
      <p class="text-brand-text/50 text-center text-sm mt-6">
        A detailed handbook is also available:
        <a href={`${base}/documents/handbok-analys-lonelots.pdf`} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="text-brand-red hover:text-brand-red-dark">Download handbook (PDF, Swedish)</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ -->
  <section id="faq" class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium text-brand-text uppercase tracking-wider mb-8 text-center">FAQ</h2>
      <div class="space-y-0 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <details class="group border-b border-gray-200">
          <summary class="cursor-pointer py-4 font-medium text-brand-text text-sm flex items-center justify-between hover:text-brand-red transition-colors">
            What does Lonelots cost?
